          </m:mrow>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>. See the text for details.)</caption></figure><para id="import-auto-id2637761">The work done by the electric field in <link target-id="import-auto-id671952"/> to move a positive charge <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>q </m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{q} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> from A, the positive plate, higher potential, to B, the negative plate, lower potential, is</para>
    <equation id="eip-554"><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>W</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mn>–Δ</m:mn><m:mtext>PE</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">–</m:mo><m:mi fontstyle="italic">q</m:mi><m:mn>Δ</m:mn><m:mi>V</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{W= - Δ"PE"= - qΔV} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></equation><para id="import-auto-id953198"> The potential difference between points A and B is</para>
    <equation id="eip-694"><m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
