          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{W= ital "qV" rSub { size 8{ ital "AB"} } } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math> 
    </equation><para id="import-auto-id1330624">Work is <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>W</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">Fd</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>cos</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{W= ital "Fd""cos"?} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>; here <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>cos</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math>, since the path is parallel to the field, and so <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>W</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">Fd</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math>. Since 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>F</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">qE</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math>, we see that <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>W</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">qEd</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math>. Substituting this expression for work into the previous equation gives</para><equation id="eip-725"><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi fontstyle="italic">qEd</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">qV</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>AB</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{qEd= ital "qV" rSub { size 8{ ital "AB"} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></equation><para id="import-auto-id2543027">The charge cancels, and so the voltage between points A and B is seen to be</para><equation id="eip-537"><m:math>
